  <title>Use the Super key</title>

  <p>When you press the <key>Super</key> key, you will be able to see your
  desktop. You can also press <key>Super</key> + <key>S</key> to see all of your
  open windows at the same time. This key can usually be found on the bottom-left
  of your keyboard, next to the <key>Alt</key> key, and usually has a
  Windows logo on it. It is sometimes called the <em>Windows key</em> or system
  key.</p>
